# Rider/Logs or user files. config others
Here's an updated and complete `.gitignore` file that includes all standard exclusions for popular IDEs like JetBrains Rider, Visual Studio, Eclipse, and others:

```gitignore
# -----------------------------
# General IDE generated files
# -----------------------------

# JetBrains Rider/IntelliJ IDEA-specific
.idea/
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.ide
.idea/**/workspace.xml
.idea/**/tasks.xml
.idea/**/dictionaries
.idea/**/shelf
.idea/**/vcs.xml
.idea/modules.xml
.idea/.idea.*
*.iml

# Rider log and index files
.idea/**/idea.log
.idea/.idea_overriden_screenshots/
.idea/**/index-layout
.idea/**/indexes/

# Eclipse-specific
.settings/
*.launch
.metadata/
.localhistory/
.recommenders/
.project
.classpath

# Visual Studio-specific
.vs/
*.vcxproj
*.vcxproj.filters
*.vcxproj.user
*.dbmdl
*.opendb
*.obj
*.lastbuildstate
*.sdf
*.ilk
*.pdb
*.ipch
[Oo]bj/
[Bb]in/
*.log

# Code::Blocks IDE
*.depend
*.layout

# MonoDevelop (also applies to Xamarin Studio)
*.userprefs

# Other common IDE temporary files
*.swp
*.ide-shm
*.ide-wal
*.tmproj
*.name
.session
*.bak
*.pid
.DS_Store  # macOS generated
Thumbs.db  # Windows generated

# --------------------------
# Editor/IDE-specific backups
# --------------------------
*.orig        # Backups generated by editors
*.log         # Log files
*.backup
*.tmp         # Temporary files
~$*           # MS Office temp files
.\#*          # Hidden auto backup in linux shells
```

This `.gitignore` file is configured to exclude files generated by IDEs as well as temporary files commonly created during developmentâ€”it ensures your Git repository remains clean and focused on actual source code only.